text":"An anterior pituitary enlargement suggests a pituitary tumor.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040761,0.087084,0.10348,0.10907,0.1048,0.098839,0.092787,0.084188,0.081295,0.074608,0.063043,0.06005],"unified_progress":[0.036667,0.070562,0.089056,0.10647,0.10424,0.10324,0.099111,0.092835,0.090026,0.080375,0.06769,0.059722]},{"section":7,"text":"The most common pituitary tumor is a prolactinoma.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033218,0.071884,0.088519,0.099982,0.10481,0.10302,0.10138,0.092794,0.084272,0.084633,0.069198,0.066293],"unified_progress":[0.032838,0.060414,0.080031,0.093112,0.098049,0.11419,0.10317,0.098696,0.093252,0.088184,0.074713,0.063346]},{"section":8,"text":"Prolactinomas are prolactin-secreting adenomas.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030373,0.065351,0.080505,0.094682,0.10394,0.106,0.10639,0.097621,0.087376,0.092077,0.070638,0.06505],"unified_progress":[0.031683,0.055792,0.077323,0.091767,0.098919,0.11074,0.10736,0.1039,0.097721,0.091191,0.074193,0.059417]},{"section":9,"text":"High prolactin levels can cause galactorrhea and disrupt the menstrual cycle, leading to irregular periods or amenorrhea.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036444,0.0733,0.080897,0.087873,0.094721,0.099053,0.10092,0.097726,0.090433,0.090421,0.07815,0.070062],"unified_progress":[0.04067,0.062839,0.074011,0.08307,0.090417,0.10119,0.099126,0.10048,0.098553,0.095141,0.085624,0.068877]},{"section":10,"text":"So the symptoms fit: hyperprolactinemia causes both the milky discharge (galactorrhea) and menstrual irregularities.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039991,0.075411,0.082664,0.087722,0.091415,0.093328,0.094845,0.093129,0.089017,0.090847,0.082196,0.079434],"unified_progress":[0.046024,0.064352,0.075085,0.0828,0.088992,0.095774,0.096147,0.097472,0.095746,0.094802,0.087107,0.0757]},{"section":11,"text":"The MRI showing pituitary enlargement supports a prolactinoma as the source.","dimension":5,"group":1,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.032896,0.071693,0.085859,0.092014,0.091489,0.091561,0.091906,0.088292,0.09352,0.087252,0.082067,0.091451],"unified_progress":[0.032029,0.060322,0.075886,0.088751,0.092504,0.094085,0.093914,0.092863,0.097087,0.090316,0.089755,0.092488]},{"section":12,"text":"Other causes of hyperprolactinemia could be medications (like antipsychotics, SSRIs), hypothyroidism, or other pituitary lesions, but given the MRI finding of enlargement, a prolactinoma is the top contender.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.030872,0.067877,0.082489,0.091656,0.096624,0.098317,0.099447,0.095879,0.091527,0.091105,0.08043,0.073777],"unified_progress":[0.033946,0.063849,0.078376,0.088028,0.094004,0.10253,0.099863,0.09856,0.096063,0.093032,0.082572,0.069173]},{"section":13,"text":"I should also consider if there are other possibilities.","dimension":12,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.029483,0.065791,0.085397,0.09321,0.096238,0.094609,0.094869,0.094001,0.092687,0.093252,0.083486,0.076978],"unified_progress":[0.035439,0.067444,0.080421,0.094094,0.095185,0.09396,0.097509,0.096034,0.09344,0.097523,0.082707,0.066244]},{"section":14,"text":"For example, a non-functioning pituitary adenoma might cause mass effects but not necessarily hyperprolactinemia.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027949,0.06362,0.078684,0.090064,0.097355,0.10083,0.10234,0.098568,0.09498,0.0923,0.081027,0.072282],"unified_progress":[0.031409,0.060481,0.078592,0.091153,0.097482,0.10431,0.10196,0.10058,0.097818,0.09209,0.078751,0.065375]},{"section":15,"text":"But the symptoms here point more towards prolactin excess.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027815,0.061034,0.076445,0.085106,0.089847,0.09166,0.095634,0.095424,0.095281,0.096801,0.091449,0.093504],"unified_progress":[0.035656,0.055343,0.068047,0.079248,0.085407,0.090508,0.093371,0.097154,0.098137,0.10183,0.099445,0.095852]},{"section":16,"text":"The bilateral galactorrhea is a classic sign.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027006,0.060395,0.075158,0.083787,0.089292,0.092196,0.09599,0.096012,0.096986,0.099234,0.095258,0.088685],"unified_progress":[0.03866,0.055911,0.06841,0.078844,0.086436,0.093716,0.096653,0.099412,0.10132,0.10365,0.096288,0.080695]},{"section":17,"text":"So I think the most likely diagnosis is a prolactinoma.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.02236,0.04578,0.056654,0.064299,0.070986,0.076543,0.083536,0.088438,0.096906,0.10235,0.11588,0.17627],"unified_progress":[0.021954,0.034147,0.04345,0.053353,0.059011,0.07205,0.076297,0.089264,0.10168,0.11054,0.1468,0.19146]}]}}